A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 2 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 elections and primaries generally, so as to authorize curbside voting for certain voters who
3 because of disability or age cannot enter a polling place or are unable to wait in line to vote;
4 to provide procedures for form, collection, and tabulation of ballots for such electors; to
5 provide for a pilot program; to revise reporting provisions to reference such ballots; to
6 provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Chapter 2 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to elections and
10 primaries generally, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
11 "21-2-409.2.
12 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of Code Section 21-2-300 to the contrary, and
13 except as otherwise provided by subsection (d) of Code Section 21-2-418, any elector who
14 because of disability or age:
15 (1) Cannot enter the polling place; or
16 (2) Is unable to wait in line to vote
