17 shall be entitled to cast a physical ballot pursuant to this Code section so as to vote outside
18 of such polling place in the closest available parking area, which shall be designated and
19 clearly marked, utilizing the vehicle in which such elector has been driven or has driven
20 to the polling place; provided, however, that such elector's name appears on the list of
21 registered electors and he or she has presented proper identification pursuant to Code
22 Section 21-2-417.
23 (b) When the poll manager at a precinct is informed that a disabled elector who cannot
24 enter the polling place or cannot wait in line to vote is exercising his or her right to cast a
25 ballot while remaining in his or her vehicle pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code section,
26 the poll manager or a poll worker shall request to review such elector's proper identification
27 as required by subsection (a) of Code Section 21-2-417. Upon verification of the elector's
28 eligibility, at least two poll workers shall take a physical voter's certificate and ballot to the
29 elector in the vehicle in the designated area outside the polling place. The poll manager
30 shall notify any poll watchers present at such precinct that a ballot will be cast pursuant to
31 subsection (a) of this Code section, and such poll watchers may, at their discretion,
32 accompany the poll workers as observers.
33 (c) No person other than the elector shall be in the vehicle in which the elector is casting
34 his or her ballot unless the elector is entitled to assistance pursuant to subsection (a) of
35 Code Section 21-2-409.
36 (d)(1) An elector qualified pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code section to cast a
37 physical ballot while remaining within his or her vehicle shall cast such ballot on the
38 same type of ballot that is used for absentee ballots pursuant to subsection (a) of Code
39 Section 21-2-383.
40 (2) Upon the elector hand marking the ballot provided for in paragraph (1) of this
41 subsection, such ballot shall not be sealed in the envelopes provided for in Code Section
42 21-2-384, but shall be folded so that the secrecy of the ballot is preserved and the elector
43 shall then return such folded ballot to the poll worker waiting outside the vehicle. The
