44 poll worker shall immediately carry such ballot inside the precinct and deposit the ballot
45 in a secure, sealed ballot box maintained for such ballots.
46 (e) Upon the closing of the polls and the last elector voting, ballots cast pursuant to this
47 Code section shall be tabulated at the precinct in the same manner provided for in Code
48 Section 21-2-483.
49 (f) The election superintendent shall provide at each polling place:
50 (1) Sufficient physical ballots, voter certificates, ballot boxes, and other necessary
51 equipment so as to allow electors opting to cast a ballot pursuant to this Code section the
52 ability to cast such ballot in secrecy;
53 (2) Sufficient equipment for the counting and tabulation of any ballots cast pursuant to
54 this Code section; and
55 (3) Designated areas for vehicles used to cast a ballot pursuant to this Code section with
56 clearly marked signage indicating such voting area.
57 (g) Notwithstanding any other provision of this Code section or other law to the contrary,
58 the Secretary of State shall conduct on the Tuesday following the first Monday in
59 November, 2025, as part of either the state-wide special general election or the general
60 municipal election, a pilot program to test and evaluate the use of curbside voting in
61 primaries and elections in this state. The Secretary of State shall review the results of such
62 pilot program and, within 90 days following such election date, shall provide the standing
63 committees of each house of the General Assembly tasked with election matters a
64 comprehensive report on the pilot program."
65 SECTION 2.
66 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 21-2-420, relating to procedure for
67 counting and tabulation of ballots, as follows:
