68 "21-2-420.
69 (a) After the time for the closing of the polls and the last elector voting, the poll officials
70 in each precinct shall complete the required accounting and related documentation for the
71 precinct and shall advise the election superintendent of the total number of ballots cast at
72 such precinct, the total number of ballots cast pursuant to Code Section 21-2-409.2, and the
73 total number of provisional ballots cast. The chief manager and at least one assistant
74 manager shall post a copy of the tabulated results for the precinct on the door of the
75 precinct and then immediately deliver all required documentation and election materials
76 to the election superintendent. The election superintendent shall then ensure that such
77 ballots are processed, counted, and tabulated as soon as possible and shall not cease such
78 count and tabulation until all such ballots are counted and tabulated.
79 (b) The election superintendent shall ensure that each precinct notifies the election
80 superintendent of the number of ballots cast, the number of ballots cast pursuant to Code
81 Section 21-2-409.2, and the number of provisional ballots cast as soon as possible after the
82 time for the closing of the polls and the last elector votes. The election superintendent shall
83 post such information publicly. The State Election Board shall promulgate rules and
84 regulations regarding how such information shall be publicly posted to ensure
85 transparency, accuracy, and security."
86 SECTION 3.
87 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
